sections.content:
“trust or fund of the Corporation” means a trust or fund established 
by  the  Corporation  to  fulfill  its  objectives  or  to  carry  out  any  of  its 
functions under the Articles of Agreement;

“chief executive officer” means a person by whatever name called 
who is responsible for the conduct of the business and administration 
of the Corporation;

(a)  the Corporation or a subsidiary conferred with the status of 
international organization under subsection 6(1), all or any 
of the privileges and immunities specified in Schedule 1;

(ii)  who was, or has ceased to perform the duties of, the 
chief  executive  officer  of  the  Corporation,  the 
immunities specified in Part II of Schedule 2;

(ii)  who was, or has ceased serving on the committee of 
the  Corporation,  the  immunities  specified  in  Part  II 
of Schedule 4;

(ii)  who was, or has ceased to perform the duties of, an 
officer  of  the  Corporation,  the  immunities  specified 
in Part II of Schedule 5;

(b)  a  civil  action  by  a  third  party  for  damage  arising  from  an 
accident  caused  by  a  motor  vehicle  or  other  means  of 
transport;

(i)  on any capital gains, reserves or income, either distributed or not, declared 
by  a  subsidiary,  a  special  purpose  vehicle  or  a  trust  or  fund  of  the 
Corporation;
